resources.string: Hello World, TesterActivity!
Memory Ladder
Instructions
In this test, you will be presented with several rows of digits. Your job is to memorize as many rows of digits as possible in the time allotted.
For each row of digits, you will earn:
1 point for each digit if there are 0 mistakes in the row.
0.5 point for each digit if there is 1 mistake in the row.
0 points if there are 2 or more mistakes in the row.
For the last row only, any spaces left blank will not count as mistakes.
The total score is the sum of each of the row scores.
In this test, you will hear a series of digits. Your job is to commit to memory and recall as many digits as possible.
One point is awarded for every correct consecutive digit, starting with the first digit of the spoken sequence.
No additional points are awarded after the first mistake.
In this test, you will be presented with several columns of random words. Your job is to commit to memory and recall as many columns of words as possible in the time allotted.
For each column of words, you will earn:
1 point for each word if there are 0 mistakes in the column.
0.5 point for each word if there is 1 mistake in the column.
0 points if there are 2 or more mistakes in the column.
Words that are clearly memorized but misspelled earn 0 points but are not counted as a mistake.
For the last row only, any spaces left blank do not count as mistakes.

In this test, you will be presented with a list of fictional events and the year in which they occurred. On the recall page, the years will be removed and the events will be shuffled. Your job is to commit to memory and recall the date of as many of the events as possible in the time allotted.
1 point is awarded for each correctly assigned year.
0.5 point is deducted for each incorrectly assigned year.

In this test, you will be presented with a series of color photographs of different people, with a first and last name printed underneath each picture. Your job is to commit to memory and recall as many names as possible and link them to the right face in the time allotted.
1 point is awarded for each correct first name and each last name.
0.5 point is awarded for each name that is clearly recalled but misspelled.
0.5 point is deducted if a name is incorrectly recalled.
0 points are awarded if a name is incorrectly recalled but is within 3 letters of the correct name.
Points are still awarded if only the first or last name is recalled.

In this test, you will be presented with several rows of abstract images, with each row containing 5 images. On the recall page, the sequence of the images will be shuffled within each individual row (the rows remain in the same order). Contestants must write a number under each image indicating its original position (reading from left to right). Your job is to commit to memory and recall the original sequence of images within as many rows as possible in the time allotted.
5 points are awarded for each correct row.
1 point is deducted for each incorrectly attempted row.
No points are awarded or deducted for rows that are not attempted.
In this test, you will be presented with several shuffled decks of cards. Your job is to commit to memory and recall as many cards as possible in the time allotted.
For each deck, you will earn:
1 point for each card if there are 0 mistakes in the deck.
0.5 point for each card if there is 1 mistake in the deck.
0 points if there are 2 or more mistakes in the deck.
For the final deck only, any cards left blank will not count as mistakes.
